[2] Romania, wild birds, identification
Date: Wed 30 Nov 2005
From: Maria Mihaita <mihaita@ansv.ro>

Re: Avian Influenza - Eurasia (85): Wild Birds, Romania
-----------------------------------------------
You have asked about the precise zoological identity of the wild birds
infected with HPAI H5, about which Romania notified the OIE (in follow-up
reports No 5, 6 and 10).
Infection has so far been detected in wild birds of 4 species. They are:
1. Lesser White-fronted Goose, _Anser erythropus_;
2. Great blue heron, _Ardea herodias_;
3. Mute swan, _Cygnus olor_;
4. Common moorhen, _Gallinula chloropus_.
--
Dr. Maria Mihaita, councelor
Animal Health Directorate, NSVFSA
<mihaita@ansv.ro>
[The information expediently provided by NSVFSA (National Sanitary
Veterinary and Food Safety Authority, Bucharest) upon our request is
gratefully acknowledged. Only one of the described species, namely the Mute
Swan, _Cygnus olor_, has been included in previous lists of infected wild
birds. Have these birds been sedentary or migratory?! This question remains
unanswered. - Mod.AS]
